Comment: The experiment was carried out at a Tandem accelerator and the target was a thin film of NaF evaporated onto a thin film of Ag. 
	 The listed uncertainties in the cross-section values are statistical and also due to peak area determination. 
	 There is a systematic uncertainty of 10% (see Sigma scale factor fields). As the gamma-ray line is isotropic the cross section values 
	 correspond to total cross section.			
			
